rtise. In particular, phrenology constructed ways of looking as well as a language for identifying, understanding, and analyzing criminals and their actions. This work traces the long-lasting influence of phrenological visual culture and language in American culture, law, and medicine, as well as the practical uses of phrenology in courts, prisons, and daily life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCriminal anthropologyzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aCriminal psychologyzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century 0aCriminal psychologyzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aCriminologyzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aPhrenologyzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 7aMEDICAL / General.2bisacsh  aHealth, Medicine, Medical Studies, Health Studies, Crime, Violence, Phrenology, 19th Century, United States, Courts, Life, Culture, Law, Prisons, Trial, Research, Criminality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073913840uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197881310640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978813106423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978813106/original  a978-3-11-073913-8  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK